snippet.title: Ex-Macquarie banker Bill Moss subleases at Chifley Tower
snippet.content:
Former Macquarie banker Bill Moss has sub-leased a 93sq m office suite at Sydney's A-grade Chifley Tower to use for his work with FSHD Global Research Foundation and Moss Home Caring, a company working with the National Disability Insurance Scheme. He will pay a gross annual rent of $1200 a square metre for the fitted-out space at 2 Chifley Square. Ray White's Naomi Vilar brokered the two-year sublease on level 12. View vantage
Amundi Asset Management has moved from 14 Martin Place to 305/25 Lime Street, King Street Wharf, after leasing a corner 221sq m office suite with views over Darling Harbour for five years.
Ray White's Andrew Edwards negotiated a gross annual rent of $820 a square metre. Toorak trade CHM Corporate Health Management has leased the 513sq m "Toorak News Agency" retail building at 485-487 Toorak Road, Toorak, in Melbourne for eight years paying a net annual rent of $300,000. Knight Frank's Paul Pellegrino and Dixon Kestles acted for landlord King Yin.
Train up Apprentice employer All Trades Queensland has secured a 1130sq m industrial property at 17 Armada Place, Banyo in Queensland ,to use for its offices and training. The property will be leased for five years with options on a net annual rent of $163,850. Colliers International's Bevan Galloway and Nick Bandiera negotiated for landlord JMCP Group.
Fantastic feat Fantastic Furniture has opened another store at a newly leased showroom retail space at Tenancy 1, 260-272 Leach Highway, Myaree in WA. A private landlord agreed to a net annual rent of just under $400,000 for the 1655sq m property over five years. Vend Property's Jeff Klopper closed the deal.
Engineering expansion Engineering business RDS International has struck a five-year lease with options for a 793sq m clear space warehouse/office in Port Melbourne to expand its Melbourne business. The property at 2 Westside Avenue, part of Portside Industrial Estate, was leased at a net annual rent of $125,000. CBRE's Guy Naselli and Jake George executed the transaction.
Defence deal Defence contractor Frazer-Nash Consultancy has leased a 127sq m office at 14 Moore Street, Canberra, to accommodate an expansion. Rents are confidential but gross annual rents in the building are about $390 to $410 a square metre. Colliers International's Aaron Bruce represented landlord Quintessential Equity. More in Moreton Bay Growing manufacturer Hiltec Glazing has taken out a bigger five-year lease over a 5794sq m office/warehouse at 14 Business Drive, Narangba, in the Moreton Bay region of Queensland. The business committed to a five-year lease for the property with a loading bay and roller-door access. CBRE's Hugh Adnam and Dillon Murphy brokered the lease.
Chatswood move Retriever Communications has moved to a newly leased 563sq m office space at Level 17, 799 Pacific Highway, Chatswood, at a net annual rent of $495 a square metre. Citadel Towers has parking, end of trip facilities and a plaza. Landlord Tackelly agreed to a five-year term through JLL's Jaime Kernaghan. Submissions to stan@fairfaxmedia.com.au
